# Workflows-test e2e MongoDB override (template)
#
# By default this app's e2e suite is SELF-CONTAINED: playwright.config.js calls
# `configureMdb(...)`, which boots an ephemeral mongodb-memory-server
# (single-node replica set, required for the engine's transactions) on a
# dedicated port and database. No external Mongo is needed.
#
# To run the suite against a REAL Mongo instead of the ephemeral memory server,
# set LOWDEFY_E2E_MONGODB_URI in your environment. When set, it overrides the
# memory server for both the served app (`_secret: MONGODB_URI`) and the `mdb`
# fixture's reads, so they share one database.
#
# Use a database name distinct from the demo's so parallel local runs do not
# collide. The target must be a replica set (transactions are required).
#
# LOWDEFY_E2E_MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/workflows_test_e2e
